  "history": "Before the Great Fog choked the heavens, Brice Alfano found his strange comfort in the intricate, predictable chaos of Romoan’s corporate world. A sharp young analyst, he navigated the actuarial tables and risk assessments of a major insurance conglomerate with a predatory grace, his mind a finely tuned instrument for extracting profit from probability. His days were a precise dance of data and high-stakes negotiation, punctuated by the quiet ritual of inhaling the pungent smoke that helped him focus, or unwind. Evenings were a fluid tapestry of connections, male and female, each liaison a fleeting distraction from the deeper game of leverage and control he played. He understood information was power, his intellect charting the precise cost of every terrestrial calamity, never once contemplating the ultimate, uninsurable ruin of a planet’s sky.\n\nThe day the sky died was not a slow twilight, but a sudden, violent tear. Brice was deep in a complex reinsurance policy, the glow of holographic projections illuminating his face, when the tremors began, not from the earth, but from above. Communication networks fractured, then screamed into static. The Great Fog descended with an unnatural, hungry speed, devouring the city in an acrid, choking shroud that stole the light and reason alike. His meticulously constructed world of calculated risks imploded. There was no actuarial table for a planet consumed by ash, no premium to cover the loss of the sun. Panic, raw and unquantifiable, replaced the orderly hum of servers. It was then, amidst the screaming and the frantic scramble, that he first found himself fighting not for profit, but for breath, a primal terror eclipsing all his learned intelligence.\n\nThe collapse that followed was swift and brutal. Brice, a man accustomed to manipulating numbers, found himself manipulating scraps of food and whispers of safe passage, his intellect now a desperate weapon for survival. Business intelligence, he quickly learned, now meant understanding who held the water, who controlled the shelters, and who could be exploited for a momentary advantage. It was during these desperate early weeks, navigating the shattered city-states, that he found himself inextricably linked to AF. Then merely a ‘servant’ in a world where titles meant little, AF proved to be an unexpected, steadfast anchor, a physical bulwark against the raw chaos while Brice assessed the shifting human landscape, their combined efforts a grim equation of immediate survival.\n\nThe years that followed were a grinding crucible. Brice shed the vestiges of corporate polish, replacing tailored suits with scavenged gear, but his mind remained sharp, honed by a relentless need to predict and exploit. He became a master of the whisper network, a conduit of information in the Ash-Trail, trading rumors for resources, forgotten intel for new world survival. His cannabis habit, once a luxury, became a grim ritual, a way to blunt the edges of a world perpetually in monochrome. He learned to leverage every advantage, be it a forgotten data chip or a fleeting alliance, his bisexuality a tool for connection or manipulation when needed, never an impediment. AF, by his side through countless dangers, had transitioned from a mere 'servant' to a constant, if sometimes exasperating, partner, a loyal shadow in the grim calculus of their shared existence, their destinies irrevocably tangled.\n\nNow, at twenty-six, Brice Alfano is a ghost in the Ash-Trail, his reputation as a \"fixer of facts\" preceding him through the City-States and the forgotten ruins. His mind constantly sifts through the dross of rumor for nuggets of truth. The recent discovery of pre-war archive fragments, hinting at functioning satellites and forgotten knowledge, has ignited a dangerous spark within him. Such information, if real, could rewrite the balance of power on Romoan, or expose secrets about the Ashfall itself – a risk he is willing to take. Others fear disturbing the sky again, but Brice sees only opportunity, a grand, unprecedented data-mining operation. It is a journey he cannot undertake alone. AF, whether they like it or not, is the key, the unwavering presence and critical partner required to navigate the perilous path towards the sky, their combined quest a defiant gamble against a world that has long forgotten its own history.",
